<h3><b>1. Cardtonic:</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cardtonic is one of the better-known gift card trading platforms in Nigeria. The platform is known for offering competitive rates across different gift card categories. Whether you want to sell your Amazon or </span><a href="https://cardtonic.com/read/buy-ebay-gift-card-with-naira-in-nigeria" data-wpel-link="exclude"><span style="font-weight: 400;">eBay gift card</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, users may receive competitive exchange rates depending on the card type and market conditions. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">What makes most gift card traders even more confident is that they can check how much their gift card is worth before selling it on Cardtonic, using the built-in rate calculator. This feature helps users compare estimated payout values before completing a transaction. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_202768" style="width: 522px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202768" class="wp-image-202768 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/oavb11620261.jpg" alt="1. Cardtonic:" width="512" height="246" /><p id="caption-attachment-202768" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Cardtonic</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can trade gift cards on the Cardtonic app or website within a few minutes, even if you are a first-time gift card trader. The process typically involves this: you provide your valid gift card details, it gets verified, and you receive your money in Naira within 5 to 15 minutes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">On the other hand, if you encounter issues during the trading process, you can contact their support team at any time, even at 2 am on Sunday, to resolve them. Continuous customer support availability may help users resolve transaction issues more quickly. </span></p>
<h3><b>2. XBanka:</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you are after instant payouts to your Nigerian bank account whenever you sell your Amazon or eBay gift card for cash, XBanka focuses on direct payouts to Nigerian bank accounts. It instantly verifies your gift card and sends its equivalent value in Naira to your preferred local account, including Zenith, First Bank, GTB, etc. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The platform emphasizes fast payout processing for completed transactions. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_202765" style="width: 522px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202765" class="wp-image-202765 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/oavb11620262.jpg" alt="2. XBanka:" width="512" height="250" /><p id="caption-attachment-202765" class="wp-caption-text">Source: XBanka</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You don’t have to worry about hidden fees or unexpected deductions in your payout when you convert gift cards on XBanka. The platform’s trading process is transparent: you can see how much your gift card is worth before you sell, and you also receive the same amount after you sell. However, you can’t trade directly on their website or app; you have to contact them via WhatsApp.</span></p>
<h3><b>3. 1MinutePay:</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1MinutePay is another reliable platform for exchanging gift cards for cash in </span><a href="https://vc4a.com/blog/2025/09/25/nigeria-to-welcome-global-investors-and-founders-to-drive-africa-s-next-wave-of-deals-and-exits/" data-wpel-link="exclude"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Nigeria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The trading process is transparent, fast, and easy.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Users can check estimated payout values before proceeding with a transaction, proceed to sell it if you are satisfied with the rate, and receive the exact amount in your preferred currency, be it Naira, Cedi, Shilling, or even Bitcoin.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202767" style="width: 522px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202767" class="wp-image-202767 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/oavb11620263.jpg" alt="3. 1MinutePay:" width="512" height="245" /><p id="caption-attachment-202767" class="wp-caption-text">Source: 1MinutePay</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">High rates are another perk you get when you sell your Amazon or eBay gift cards for cash on 1MinutePay. The platform advertises competitive exchange rates for supported gift cards. </span></p>
<h3><b>4. Astro Africa:</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Astro Africa may appeal to first-time users looking for a simplified trading interface. The platform has an easy-to-navigate interface, which makes even first-time gift card traders confidently sell their gift cards for cash.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Whether you want to sell your Amazon or eBay gift card for cash or convert it to </span><a href="https://vc4a.com/mercy-corps-social-venture-fund/crypto-for-good-fund/" data-wpel-link="exclude"><span style="font-weight: 400;">cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, you can complete the trading process in 10 to 15 minutes on the Astro Africa app or website.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202766" style="width: 522px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202766" class="wp-image-202766 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/oavb11620264.jpg" alt="4. Astro Africa:" width="512" height="253" /><p id="caption-attachment-202766" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Astro Africa</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Trading your gift cards on Astro Africa also helps you earn more profits. For instance, the rates of gift cards like Amazon and eBay are higher than those on some other platforms. It also sends in-app notifications whenever gift card rates are high, which usually comes in handy because timing matters when trading gift cards for cash. </span></p>
<h3><b>5. TradeCard:</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">TradeCard is a dedicated gift card platform in Nigeria, where you can sell your Amazon or eBay gift cards for cash and also buy other top gift cards with Naira. This flexibility makes it the go-to app for seasoned gift card traders in Nigeria, as they can confidently flip any gift cards without hassles.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Beyond the flexibility, every gift card transaction on the Trade Card app is secure. It uses bank-level encryption to prevent bad actors from accessing your money and financial data.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202764" style="width: 522px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202764" class="wp-image-202764 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/oavb11620265.jpg" alt="5. TradeCard:" width="512" height="250" /><p id="caption-attachment-202764" class="wp-caption-text">Source: TradeCard</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">TradeCard also includes a bonus points and referral system. Aside from the fact that you get to sell at high rates, you also get a bonus point every time you trade, which you can add to your next payout and earn more money. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It also offers a referral system that offers you up to ₦1,500 for every successful referral. The more you refer your friends to trade on the app, the higher your reward. </span></p>
<h2><b>How to Sell Amazon and eBay Gift Cards for Cash in Nigeria</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To sell Amazon and eBay gift cards for cash in Nigeria, choose a reliable gift card platform like Cardtonic, visit the official website, and create a new account. Then, navigate to the “Sell Gift Card” option and follow the on-screen instructions to complete the process.</span></p>
<p><b>Step 1: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Visit the Cardtonic website or download the app on the Play Store or App Store.</span></p>
<p><b>Step 2: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Log in to your account or create a new one.</span></p>
<p><b>Step 3:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Navigate to the “Sell Gift Card” option.</span></p>
<p><b>Step 4:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Provide your Amazon or eBay gift card details, including the category, subcategory, amount, and gift card code.</span></p>
<p><b>Step 5: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Review the details and click the “Proceed” button. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Follow the onscreen instructions to complete the process. Once your transaction is successful, you’ll receive an instant notification, and your wallet balance will be topped up. </span></p>
<h3><b>FAQ: Selling Amazon and eBay Gift Cards in Nigeria </b></h3>
<h3><b>How Much is a $100 Amazon Gift Card in Nigerian Money?</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The price of an </span><a href="https://cardtonic.com/read/100-dollar-amazon-gift-card-nigerian-naira" data-wpel-link="exclude"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Amazon card of $100</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">in naira varies based on factors like currency exchange rates, the type of your Amazon gift card, and even where you want to sell it. For instance, the price of a $100 physical Amazon gift card is between ₦55,000 and ₦58,000. However, an $100 Amazon e-gift card is between ₦28,000 and ₦40,000.</span></p>
<h3><b>How Do I Check an eBay Gift Card Balance?</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To check your </span><a href="https://cardtonic.com/read/check-ebay-gift-card-balance" data-wpel-link="exclude"><span style="font-weight: 400;">eBay gift card balance</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, visit the official eBay gift card balance checker, enter your 13-digit gift card code, and click the “Check Balance” button to view the remaining balance.</span></p>
<h3><b>What Should Users Consider When Choosing a Gift Card Platform in Nigeria? </b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cardtonic is one of several widely used gift card trading platforms in Nigeria. This platform is trusted by thousands of Nigerian gift card traders and offers high rates that help you earn more profits whenever you sell your gift cards.</span></p>
<h3><b>What is the Current eBay Gift Card Rate​ in Naira?</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The current eBay gift card rate in Naira is between ₦670 and ₦800 per dollar. However, it varies depending on the gift card type (e-gift or physical), the amount, and the gift card platform.</span></p>
<h3><b>Which Platforms Support Gift Card Redemption in Nigeria? </b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can use a reliable gift card app like Cardtonic to redeem your gift cards in Nigeria. This platform offers one of the highest rates in the market, pays you the equivalent of your gift card in Naira, and offers 24/7 customer support whenever you encounter issues.</span></p>
<h2><b>Conclusion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You don’t have to review twenty gift card platforms before you know the safest one to sell your Amazon or eBay gift card for cash.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This guide has made the process much easier, highlighting the top 6 sites to sell gift cards in Nigeria.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Whether you choose to sell your Amazon and eBay gift cards on Cardtonic, XBanka, or 1MinutePay, users can compare rates, payout speed, and platform features based on their preferences. Platforms like Astro Africa and TradeCard also offer high rates and payout in various local currencies, including Naira.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Users prioritizing payout speed, support availability, and rate transparency may consider comparing Cardtonic with other platforms listed in this guide. </span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/5-platforms-to-sell-amazon-and-ebay-gift-cards-for-cash-in-nigeria/" data-wpel-link="internal">5 Platforms to Sell Amazon and eBay Gift Cards for Cash in Nigeria </a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
